[2] Fox, human exposure - North Carolina
Date: 7 Nov 2012
Source: WSPA.com [edited]
http://www2.wspa.com/news/2012/nov/07/fox-tests-positive-rabies-after-biting-man-polk-co-ar-4916575/


A fox has tested positive for rabies in Polk County after biting a man last week. Officials say the fox bit a man while he was working on a horse farm off John Smith Road in the Green Creek community.

The Polk County Sheriff's Office got the results from the state veterinarian Tuesday [6 Nov 2012] that the fox tested positive for rabies. This is the 3rd rabid animal found in Polk County this year [2012].

Two horses in the area of the rabid fox will be monitored for the next 6 months to ensure their health. No bite marks were found on the animals.

A rabies vaccination clinic has been scheduled on 17 Nov 2012 at the Green Creek Fire Department [presumably for dogs & cats? The man has presumably already been vaccinated. - Mod.JW].

[Byline: Emily Pace]

